    "EDITORIAL PAGE Vol BNo 210 THE MILWAUKEE LEADER Published every evening except Sunday by the Milwaukee SocialDemocrat Publishing Company at Chestnut and Sixth Streets VICTOR L BERGER Editor On indefinite leave of absence and not responsible for the content of this Associate Editors E H THOMAS JOHN M WORK OSCAR AMERINGER SUBSCRIPTION RATESThe mail edition of The Milwaukee Leader will b ent to any subscriber in the United States under 3rd class postage for 70 cents per month 190 for three months 380 for six months 760 for one year The Home Edition will be delivered in Milwaukee and suburbs for 10c a week er 40c a month If the delivery of your paper is not regular notify the circulation depart ment Grand 6060 immediately and your complaint will be promptly attended to Office Hour Barnto6pro el Grand 5060 thefallingdollar The Illinois postmastersin a resolution which we publish elsewhere recognize the decreased purchasing power of the dollar They ask for an increase of compensation accordingly Most of them are middle class mennot wage workers but men who stepped from some local business into the postmaster ship They belong to the class of people who are often irritated when workingmen ask"
